{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"73f27118-3372-49ea-b251-97c44aa64521","content":"The issue is the file compilation order in the `.fsproj`. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules defined in files listed **before** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` is listed first.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_GC7b6o7aVZdL7PU3lfRuhe","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-461c8dc17aab4cfa9b09ec5f148c8ed4/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-461c8dc17aab4cfa9b09ec5f148c8ed4/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"f0d4ca43-d014-49bd-adce-326498ca122d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *before* them in the .fsproj. \n\nThe current order in the `.fsproj` is:\n1. `Services.fs` \n2. `Domain.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. The correct order should be:\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":440,"requestId":"5C01:27A376:1DBF298:21919BB:6A07C8BA"},"id":"65b8050a-8676-4040-b185-85da349289fc","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:30:42.064Z","parentId":"d5a35b49-4518-499e-a569-2230de38b2da"}
